==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hornblende
<hw>Horn"blende`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G., fr.
<ets>horn</ets> horn + <ets>blende</ets> blende.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>The common black, or dark green or brown, variety
of amphibole. (See <er>Amphibole</er>.) It belongs to the aluminous
division of the species, and is also characterized by its containing
considerable iron. Also used as a general term to include the whole
species.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hornblende schist</b></col> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>, <cd>a
hornblende rock of schistose structure.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hornblendic</ent>⟦br⟧
